syntax macros and extended translation.wa translation approach is described which allowsone to extended the syntax and semantics of a given high-level base language by the use of a newformalism called a syntax-macro.  syntax-macros define string transformations based on syntactic elementsof the base language.  two types of macros are discussed, and examples are given of their use.  theconditional generation of macros based on options and alternatives recognized by the scan are also described.cacm november, leavenworth, b. m.ca jb march ,   : pm